articles.author: Loren Grush
articles.title: SpaceX successfully launches four astronauts on Crew-3 mission to the space station - The Verge
articles.description: On November 10th, SpaceX launched another crew of four astronauts to the International Space Station on the company’s Crew-3 mission for NASA. Three NASA astronauts and one German astronaut with the European Space Agency will stay for six months on the ISS.
articles.content:
The crew lifted off at 9:03PM ET

articles.title: EU accuses Belarus of 'trafficking' migrants toward border - CTV News
articles.description: European Union officials on Wednesday accused Belarus of state-sponsored 'trafficking' of human lives by luring desperate migrants to the Polish border - the edge of the EU - where many are now stuck in makeshift camps in freezing weather.
